forePnniGroup.description: This module implements the FORE Systems extentions to the PNNI MIB.

pnniPcProfileType.name: pnniPcProfileType
pnniPcProfileType.description: Indicates whether the profile is dynamic generated or user configured for cache profile there might be avoid node list or prefered node list

pnniPcProfileOptCTD.name: pnniPcProfileOptCTD
pnniPcProfileOptCTD.description: optimization criteria flag: Multiple trees will be computed for VBR if several are set. For ABR profile, only one of these can be set. If CTD set, CDV is treated as path constraint. Only one can be set of AW and CAW

pnniPcProfileRstrLoadBalance.name: pnniPcProfileRstrLoadBalance
pnniPcProfileRstrLoadBalance.description: for ABR/UBR. True means do not load-balance trees

pnniPcProfileNumberOfAvoidLinks.name: pnniPcProfileNumberOfAvoidLinks
pnniPcProfileNumberOfAvoidLinks.description: number of avoided links in this profile for cache profile only

pnniPcProfileNumberOfPreferLinks.name: pnniPcProfileNumberOfPreferLinks
pnniPcProfileNumberOfPreferLinks.description: number of preferred links in this profile for cache profile only

pnniPcProfileNumberOfHits.name: pnniPcProfileNumberOfHits
pnniPcProfileNumberOfHits.description: number of hits on this profile since it is configured

pnniPcProfileTimeStamp.name: pnniPcProfileTimeStamp
pnniPcProfileTimeStamp.description: Time elapsed since last hit in seconds

pnniPcProfileState.name: pnniPcProfileState
pnniPcProfileState.description: State of the profile, whether it is computed, in computing or topolgy changed

pnniPcProfileRowStatus.name: pnniPcProfileRowStatus
pnniPcProfileRowStatus.description: for create, modify and delete a profile entry

pnniPcProfileCongestionBased.name: pnniPcProfileCongestionBased
pnniPcProfileCongestionBased.description: Indicates if the profile describes a congestion based route

pnniNodeExtnTable.name: pnniNodeExtnTable
pnniNodeExtnTable.description: Extension to the PNNI Node Table in the PNNI MIB

pnniNodeExtnDomainID.name: pnniNodeExtnDomainID
pnniNodeExtnDomainID.description: The ID of the ATM Routing Domain to which this PNNI Node belongs

pnniNodeExtnForeLevel.name: pnniNodeExtnForeLevel
pnniNodeExtnForeLevel.description: The level of the area to which this PNNI node belongs in the FORE hierarchy

pnniNodeExtnForeArea.name: pnniNodeExtnForeArea
pnniNodeExtnForeArea.description: the ID of the area in the FORE hierarchy to which this PNNI node belongs

pnniNodeExtnShutdown.name: pnniNodeExtnShutdown
pnniNodeExtnShutdown.description: Specifies whether the node is shutdown or not due to inconsistencies in TDB or due to TDB incremental MALLOC failures.A value of false indicates that the PNNI logical node is not shutdown and participates in all PNNI Protocol operation(s),and a value of true indicates that PNNI logical node is Shutdown and the switch has to be rebooted to bring this PNNI logical node up again.

pnniNodeExtnLoadBalancing.name: pnniNodeExtnLoadBalancing
pnniNodeExtnLoadBalancing.description: Specifies whether the profiles creating during on demand path computation are load balanced.

pnniNodeExtnAdvertisedPglPriority.name: pnniNodeExtnAdvertisedPglPriority
pnniNodeExtnAdvertisedPglPriority.description: This is the leadership priority value which is actually advertised by the node. This can differ from the configured value for reasons of PGL/LGN-incapability or stability.

pnniNodeExtnPcCongestionRange.name: pnniNodeExtnPcCongestionRange
pnniNodeExtnPcCongestionRange.description: The range in congestion that path computation will include in a profile tree

pnniMapRaigIndex.name: pnniMapRaigIndex
pnniMapRaigIndex.description: An index into set of RAIG entries in the MAP entry. For Horizontal Links and Up Links only outgoing RAIG entries are present. For Nodal State IGs RAIG entries are present for both directions.

pnniMapRaigDirection.name: pnniMapRaigDirection
pnniMapRaigDirection.description: The direction of the link for which this particular set of parameters

pnniMapRaigFlags.name: pnniMapRaigFlags
pnniMapRaigFlags.description: Bit mask identifying which service category this RAIG describes. The GCAC CLP Attribute bit is also present.

pnniMapRaigAdminWt.name: pnniMapRaigAdminWt
pnniMapRaigAdminWt.description: Adminstrative Weight associated with this map entry.

pnniMapRaigCellLossRatio.name: pnniMapRaigCellLossRatio
pnniMapRaigCellLossRatio.description: Cell Loss Ratio for CLP=0 encoded as the negative logarithm of the value.

pnniMapRaigCellLossRatio1.name: pnniMapRaigCellLossRatio1
pnniMapRaigCellLossRatio1.description: Cell Loss Ratio for CLP=0+1 encoded as the negative logarithm of the value.

pnniMapRaigCellRateMargin.name: pnniMapRaigCellRateMargin
pnniMapRaigCellRateMargin.description: Cell Rate Margin in units cells/second. If the optional GCAC related information is not present then this value would be set to zero.

pnniMapRaigVarianceFactor.name: pnniMapRaigVarianceFactor
pnniMapRaigVarianceFactor.description: Variance Factor in units 2^-8. If the optional GCAC related information is not present then this value would be set to zero.

pnniMapAddrRaigIndex.name: pnniMapAddrRaigIndex
pnniMapAddrRaigIndex.description: An index into set of RAIG entries in the MapAddr entry. For Horizontal Links and Up Links only outgoing RAIG entries are present. For Nodal State IGs RAIG entries are present for both directions.

pnniMapAddrRaigDirection.name: pnniMapAddrRaigDirection
pnniMapAddrRaigDirection.description: The direction of the link for which this particular set of parameters

pnniMapAddrRaigFlags.name: pnniMapAddrRaigFlags
pnniMapAddrRaigFlags.description: Bit mask identifying which service category this RAIG describes. The GCAC CLP Attribute bit is also present.

pnniMapAddrRaigAdminWt.name: pnniMapAddrRaigAdminWt
pnniMapAddrRaigAdminWt.description: Adminstrative Weight associated with this MapAddr entry.

pnniMapAddrRaigCellLossRatio.name: pnniMapAddrRaigCellLossRatio
pnniMapAddrRaigCellLossRatio.description: Cell Loss Ratio for CLP=0 encoded as the negative logarithm of the value.

pnniMapAddrRaigCellLossRatio1.name: pnniMapAddrRaigCellLossRatio1
pnniMapAddrRaigCellLossRatio1.description: Cell Loss Ratio for CLP=0+1 encoded as the negative logarithm of the value.

pnniMapAddrRaigCellRateMargin.name: pnniMapAddrRaigCellRateMargin
pnniMapAddrRaigCellRateMargin.description: Cell Rate Margin in units cells/second. If the optional GCAC related information is not present then this value would be set to zero.

pnniMapAddrRaigVarianceFactor.name: pnniMapAddrRaigVarianceFactor
pnniMapAddrRaigVarianceFactor.description: Variance Factor in units 2^-8. If the optional GCAC related information is not present then this value would be set to zero.

pnniPcProfileMapOptIndex.name: pnniPcProfileMapOptIndex
pnniPcProfileMapOptIndex.description: An index into set of RAIG entries in the MapAddr entry. For Horizontal Links and Up Links only outgoing RAIG entries are present. For Nodal State IGs RAIG entries are present for both directions.

pnniPcProfileMapNodeId.name: pnniPcProfileMapNodeId
pnniPcProfileMapNodeId.description: The nodes on the precomputed paths tree.

pnniPcProfileMapLocalPort.name: pnniPcProfileMapLocalPort
pnniPcProfileMapLocalPort.description: The local port the this node connects to the remote node

pnniPcProfileMapAdminWt.name: pnniPcProfileMapAdminWt
pnniPcProfileMapAdminWt.description: Adminstrative Weight associated with this MapAddr entry.

pnniPcProfileMapCellLossRatio.name: pnniPcProfileMapCellLossRatio
pnniPcProfileMapCellLossRatio.description: Cell Loss Ratio for CLP=0 encoded as the negative logarithm of the value.

pnniPcProfileMapCellLossRatio1.name: pnniPcProfileMapCellLossRatio1
pnniPcProfileMapCellLossRatio1.description: Cell Loss Ratio for CLP=0+1 encoded as the negative logarithm of the value.

pnniPcProfileMapCellRateMargin.name: pnniPcProfileMapCellRateMargin
pnniPcProfileMapCellRateMargin.description: Cell Rate Margin in units cells/second. If the optional GCAC related information is not present then this value would be set to zero.

pnniPcProfileMapVarianceFactor.name: pnniPcProfileMapVarianceFactor
pnniPcProfileMapVarianceFactor.description: Variance Factor in units 2^-8. If the optional GCAC related information is not present then this value would be set to zero.

pnniSpanningTreeMapNodeId.name: pnniSpanningTreeMapNodeId
pnniSpanningTreeMapNodeId.description: The nodes on the Reachability tree.

pnniSpanningTreeMapStatus.name: pnniSpanningTreeMapStatus
pnniSpanningTreeMapStatus.description: The status of the spanning tree. If links are added or removed then the spanning tree may not be up to date for a while until the tree is updated. If there are link added and deleted, the status will be linkdeleted

pnniSpanningTreeMapParentNode.name: pnniSpanningTreeMapParentNode
pnniSpanningTreeMapParentNode.description: The parent node or the next hop node on the spanning tree

pnniSpanningTreeMapPort.name: pnniSpanningTreeMapPort
pnniSpanningTreeMapPort.description: The local port the this node connects to the remote node

pnniSpanningTreeMapLinkType.name: pnniSpanningTreeMapLinkType
pnniSpanningTreeMapLinkType.description: The type of the link that connects this noe to the remote node

pnniConnTreeMapNodeId.name: pnniConnTreeMapNodeId
pnniConnTreeMapNodeId.description: The nodes on the Connectivity tree.

pnniConnTreeMapStatus.name: pnniConnTreeMapStatus
pnniConnTreeMapStatus.description: The status of the connectivity tree. If links are added or removed then the tree may not be up to date for a while until the tree is updated. If there are link added and deleted, the status will be linkdeleted

pnniConnTreeMapParentNode.name: pnniConnTreeMapParentNode
pnniConnTreeMapParentNode.description: The parent node or the next hop node on the tree

pnniConnTreeMapPort.name: pnniConnTreeMapPort
pnniConnTreeMapPort.description: The local port the this node connects to the remote node

pnniConnTreeMapLinkType.name: pnniConnTreeMapLinkType
pnniConnTreeMapLinkType.description: The type of the link that connects this noe to the remote node

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfPurges.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfPurges
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfPurges.description: The number of scheduler queue purges

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfTimeoutPurges.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfTimeoutPurges
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfTimeoutPurges.description: The number of times scheduler queues were purged due to xxx timer expiry.

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfPacketsDropped.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfPacketsDropped
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfPacketsDropped.description: The number of packets dropped in the scheduler

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfHiPriPktsDropped.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfHiPriPktsDropped
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfHiPriPktsDropped.description: The number of high priority packets dropped in the scheduler

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfLowPriPktsDropped.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfLowPriPktsDropped
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfLowPriPktsDropped.description: The number of low priority packets dropped in the scheduler

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfNodalInfoEvents.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfNodalInfoEvents
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfNodalInfoEvents.description: The number of significant changes occurred to NodalInformation Information Groups

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfHorizLinkEvents.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfHorizLinkEvents
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfHorizLinkEvents.description: The number of significant changes occurred to Horizontal Link Information Group.

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfUpLinkEvents.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfUpLinkEvents
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfUpLinkEvents.description: The number of significant changes occurred to Uplink Information Group.

pnniNodeScStatsNrOfNodalStateEvents.name: pnniNodeScStatsNrOfNodalStateEvents
pnniNodeScStatsNrOfNodalStateEvents.description: The number of significant changes occurred to Nodal State Information Group.

pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkTable.name: pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkTable
pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkTable.description: avoid link table for the cache profile

pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkIndex.name: pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkIndex
pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkIndex.description: The index to the list of to be avoided links in this profile

pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkNodeId.name: pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkNodeId
pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkNodeId.description: The nodeid of the node to be avoided

pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkPortId.name: pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkPortId
pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkPortId.description: Portid of the link. If it is zero, the node is to be avoided which means all links of this node should be avoided

pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkType.name: pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkType
pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkType.description: The link type, normal link will in the form of (node, portid, rmtnode) for reverse link it is in form of (node, rmtportid, rmtnode) and it is the reverse reprentation of the uplink (rmtnode, rmtportid, node)

pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkRemoteNodeId.name: pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkRemoteNodeId
pnniPcProfileAvoidLinkRemoteNodeId.description: The remote node id of the link. If portid is zero, then the node is to be avoided not just a link. Remote node id is not available in this case

pnniPcProfilePreferLinkTable.name: pnniPcProfilePreferLinkTable
pnniPcProfilePreferLinkTable.description: Prefered link table for the cache profile

pnniPcProfilePreferLinkIndex.name: pnniPcProfilePreferLinkIndex
pnniPcProfilePreferLinkIndex.description: The index to the list of prefered links in this profile

pnniPcProfilePreferLinkNodeId.name: pnniPcProfilePreferLinkNodeId
pnniPcProfilePreferLinkNodeId.description: The nodeid of the node is prefered

pnniPcProfilePreferLinkType.name: pnniPcProfilePreferLinkType
pnniPcProfilePreferLinkType.description: The link type, normal link will in the form of (node, portid, rmtnode) for reverse link it is in form of (node, rmtportid, rmtnode) and it is the reverse reprentation of the uplink (rmtnode, rmtportid, node)

pnniPcProfilePreferLinkRemoteNodeId.name: pnniPcProfilePreferLinkRemoteNodeId
pnniPcProfilePreferLinkRemoteNodeId.description: The remote node id of the link.

pnniDtlListTable.name: pnniDtlListTable
pnniDtlListTable.description: This table contains a list of Designated Transit Lists (DTLs) and their associated weights.

pnniDtlListEntry.name: pnniDtlListEntry
pnniDtlListEntry.description: An entry in the PNNI DTL list table. A DTL list is formed by concatenating rows of the table for which the pnniDtlListIndex is the same.

pnniDtlListTag.name: pnniDtlListTag
pnniDtlListTag.description: The value of this object specifies the tag associated with a PNNI DTL list in the table. A DTL list is a list of source route entries.

pnniDtlListNodeIndex.name: pnniDtlListNodeIndex
pnniDtlListNodeIndex.description: A unique pre-configured DTL on a switch is identified by a nodeIndex, dtlIndex pair. This object corresponds to the nodeIndex value of the DTL being referred to.

pnniDtlListDtlIndex.name: pnniDtlListDtlIndex
pnniDtlListDtlIndex.description: A unique pre-configured DTL on a switch is identified by a nodeIndex, dtlIndex pair. This object corresponds to the dtlIndex value of the DTL being referred to.

pnniDtlListWeight.name: pnniDtlListWeight
pnniDtlListWeight.description: The weight specifies the priority of this DTL entry index among all the DTL indices that are specified in the list.

pnniDtlListStatus.name: pnniDtlListStatus
pnniDtlListStatus.description: The status of this DTL entry in the list.

forePnniDTLTable.name: forePnniDTLTable
forePnniDTLTable.description: This table holds the validate object for the DTL entries defined in the standard PNNI DTL MIB table.

forePnniDTLEntry.name: forePnniDTLEntry
forePnniDTLEntry.description: Validate command for the DTL indexed by the node and DTL index.

forePnniDTLName.name: forePnniDTLName
forePnniDTLName.description: The Name of this Directed Designated Transit List

forePnniDTLValidity.name: forePnniDTLValidity
forePnniDTLValidity.description: The validity of the DTL referenced by the pnniNodeIndex and pnniDtlIndex. If validation fails, the text describes the cause for failure and the hop at which the dtl failed.

pnniDtlComputationTable.name: pnniDtlComputationTable
pnniDtlComputationTable.description: This table provides an interface for the calculation and creation of a DTL.

pnniDtlComputationEntry.name: pnniDtlComputationEntry
pnniDtlComputationEntry.description: A structure containing the parameters for creation of a directed DTL.

pnniDtlComputationNodeIndex.name: pnniDtlComputationNodeIndex
pnniDtlComputationNodeIndex.description: The node index of the DTL to be created.

pnniDtlComputationDtlIndex.name: pnniDtlComputationDtlIndex
pnniDtlComputationDtlIndex.description: The DTL index of the DTL to be created.

pnniDtlComputationDestNsapAddress.name: pnniDtlComputationDestNsapAddress
pnniDtlComputationDestNsapAddress.description: The destination NSAP address of the DTL to be created.

pnniDtlComputationCompute.name: pnniDtlComputationCompute
pnniDtlComputationCompute.description: When this object is written to, an attempt will be made to compute and create a new DTL with the specified parameters.

pnniMaxCrankbackTries.name: pnniMaxCrankbackTries
pnniMaxCrankbackTries.description: The maximum number of tries for a given call in the case of receiving crankbacks when attempting to progress the call. This value includes the first attempt at progressing the call also.

pnniMaxDtlSize.name: pnniMaxDtlSize
pnniMaxDtlSize.description: The maximum number of hops per DTL supported by this switch. The switch will not process any incoming DTL that has more than this number of hops at any level of the PNNI hierarchy. It will also not generate any calls with more than this number of hops in any DTL at any level of PNNI hierarchy.

pnniLoadBalancedUbrEnable.name: pnniLoadBalancedUbrEnable
pnniLoadBalancedUbrEnable.description: This value specifies whether LBUBR routing of SPVCs is enabled

rtDomainTable.name: rtDomainTable
rtDomainTable.description: A table of routing domains withing the ATM routing module

rtDomainEntry.name: rtDomainEntry
rtDomainEntry.description: A table entry containing administrative routing domain information

rtDomainID.name: rtDomainID
rtDomainID.description: The ID of this Routing Domain

rtDomainDefaultProto.name: rtDomainDefaultProto
rtDomainDefaultProto.description: The Default routing protocol used by this switch

rtDomainPrefix.name: rtDomainPrefix
rtDomainPrefix.description: The Default Prefix associated with this Domain

rtDomainName.name: rtDomainName
rtDomainName.description: The Domain Name of this administrative Routing Domain

rtDomainDefSumState.name: rtDomainDefSumState
rtDomainDefSumState.description: The State of the Default Summarization Policy in this domain. If enabled, Default Summarization Policies are activated (peergroup ID of each node in this domain is used as a summarization policy for all other nodes in the domain). If disabled, the default summarization policies are deactivated

rtDomainStatus.name: rtDomainStatus
rtDomainStatus.description: The entry status of this routing domain

rtDomainDefaultPrefix.name: rtDomainDefaultPrefix
rtDomainDefaultPrefix.description: The factory-encoded default domain prefix for this switch

atmrPrefixTable.name: atmrPrefixTable
atmrPrefixTable.description: The atmrPrefixTable is a collection of all addresses reachable with in a domain. This includes all internal reachable addresses, external reachable addresses and locally registered addresses.

atmrPrefixEntry.name: atmrPrefixEntry
atmrPrefixEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a reachable prefix in this switching system.

atmrPrefixAddr.name: atmrPrefixAddr
atmrPrefixAddr.description: The value of the prefix. In the case where multiple nodes advertised reachability to the same prefix, all the PTEs describes the nodes will be collected in this entry.

atmrPrefixFlags.name: atmrPrefixFlags
atmrPrefixFlags.description: Flags indicate the status of the prefix node, this is a bitmask. The description of bits is as follows. Bit Description 1 when set indicates that this prefix node in on the change list 2 when set indicates that the prefix node has been deleted.

atmrPrefixOwnerLevel.name: atmrPrefixOwnerLevel
atmrPrefixOwnerLevel.description: The level of the node that owns this prefix. The meaning of owning a prefix can be explained as the preferred node among the nodes advertising this prefix.

atmrPrefixOwnerProtocol.name: atmrPrefixOwnerProtocol
atmrPrefixOwnerProtocol.description: The protocol throught which this prefix was learnt from the owner.

atmrPrefixOwnerPathFlags.name: atmrPrefixOwnerPathFlags
atmrPrefixOwnerPathFlags.description: These flags describe the status of the PTE that owns it. Bit Description 1 when set indicates that this PTE is locally originated and cannot be further summarized.

atmrPteTable.name: atmrPteTable
atmrPteTable.description: The atmrPteTable collects all the PTEs that are present in the Prefix Table. There is single row for every address known for each source.

atmrPteEntry.name: atmrPteEntry
atmrPteEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a reachable address, source and a handle to the source

atmrPteIndex.name: atmrPteIndex
atmrPteIndex.description: Index to list of ptes belong to this prefix node

atmrPteProtocolId.name: atmrPteProtocolId
atmrPteProtocolId.description: Protocol's reference/identifier that the exact source of this information. It is tdbhndl for PNNI and nothing for ilmi or other localy registred addresses.

atmrPteProtocolHandle.name: atmrPteProtocolHandle
atmrPteProtocolHandle.description: Protocol's internal handle for this PTE, for pnni it is ptsehndl and for local routes it is the rt_node.

atmrPteProtocol.name: atmrPteProtocol
atmrPteProtocol.description: The protocol through which this prefix was learnt.

atmrPtePathFlags.name: atmrPtePathFlags
atmrPtePathFlags.description: These flags describe the status of the PTE that owns it. Bit Description 1 when set indicates that this PTE is locally originated and cannot be further summarized.

atmrPteLevel.name: atmrPteLevel
atmrPteLevel.description: The area level of the registerer.

atmrPteArea.name: atmrPteArea
atmrPteArea.description: The id of are to which registerer belongs to.

atmrPteSourceArea.name: atmrPteSourceArea
atmrPteSourceArea.description: The id of area from which prefix was learned.

atmrPteType.name: atmrPteType
atmrPteType.description: the reachability type of the prefix, its either internal ot external.

atmrPteTnsLen.name: atmrPteTnsLen
atmrPteTnsLen.description: The length of the TNS ID.

atmrPteTnsType.name: atmrPteTnsType
atmrPteTnsType.description: Indicates the type of network identification of a specified transit network.

atmrPteTnsPlan.name: atmrPteTnsPlan
atmrPteTnsPlan.description: Indicates the network identification plan of a specified transit network.

atmrPteTnsId.name: atmrPteTnsId
atmrPteTnsId.description: The identifier of the transit network.

atmrInterDomainRouteTable.name: atmrInterDomainRouteTable
atmrInterDomainRouteTable.description: A table of static inter-domain routes within the ATMR module

atmrInterDomainRouteEntry.name: atmrInterDomainRouteEntry
atmrInterDomainRouteEntry.description: A table entry containing an inter-domain static route

atmrIDRDomainID.name: atmrIDRDomainID
atmrIDRDomainID.description: The ID of this Routing Domain to which this static route belongs. This static route gets installed in the Prefix Tree of this domain and gets exported all nodes (PNNI and FT-PNNI) operating in this domain

atmrIDRAddr.name: atmrIDRAddr
atmrIDRAddr.description: This is the ATM Addr Prefix which is the reachable address prefix

atmrIDRAddrLen.name: atmrIDRAddrLen
atmrIDRAddrLen.description: The prefix length to be applied to the ATM address prefix

atmrIDRDestDomainID.name: atmrIDRDestDomainID
atmrIDRDestDomainID.description: The ID of the destination Domain in which this reachable prefix is actually reachable

atmrIDRRowStatus.name: atmrIDRRowStatus
atmrIDRRowStatus.description: To create, delete, activate and de-activate a Inter-Domain route entries.

atmrDestNsapTable.name: atmrDestNsapTable
atmrDestNsapTable.description: A table of containing NSAP addresses for each AtmIf in a routing domain. This is used for SPVCCs and SPVPCs.

atmrDestNsapEntry.name: atmrDestNsapEntry
atmrDestNsapEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing the NSAP address for the AtmIf in a domain.

atmrDestNsapAddr.name: atmrDestNsapAddr
atmrDestNsapAddr.description: The NSAP address of this AtmIf in this domain.

pnniPortVpiMapTable.name: pnniPortVpiMapTable
pnniPortVpiMapTable.description: Hardware Port table for converting Port VPI to ifix and portid in pnni

pnniPortIdMapTable.name: pnniPortIdMapTable
pnniPortIdMapTable.description: Port ID map table for converting Port ID to port/vpi and ifix

pnniPortIdMapPortId.name: pnniPortIdMapPortId
pnniPortIdMapPortId.description: PNNI Port ID corresponding the interface

pnniMapNodeExtTable.name: pnniMapNodeExtTable
pnniMapNodeExtTable.description: A table containing extended map node information for PNNI nodes running on FORE switches

pnniMapNodeExtEntry.name: pnniMapNodeExtEntry
pnniMapNodeExtEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing the extended map node information for a particular node.

pnniMapNodeExtRemoteNodeId.name: pnniMapNodeExtRemoteNodeId
pnniMapNodeExtRemoteNodeId.description: The PNNI node ID of the node being described.

pnniMapNodeExtSoftwareVersion.name: pnniMapNodeExtSoftwareVersion
pnniMapNodeExtSoftwareVersion.description: The version number of the software on the host switch

pnniMapNodeExtHardwareVersion.name: pnniMapNodeExtHardwareVersion
pnniMapNodeExtHardwareVersion.description: The version number of the hardware on the host switch

pnniMapNodeExtHardwareId.name: pnniMapNodeExtHardwareId
pnniMapNodeExtHardwareId.description: A value uniquely identifying the host switch

pnniMapNodeExtSwitchName.name: pnniMapNodeExtSwitchName
pnniMapNodeExtSwitchName.description: The system name of the host switch

pnniMapNodeExtRemoteNodeIndex.name: pnniMapNodeExtRemoteNodeIndex
pnniMapNodeExtRemoteNodeIndex.description: The node index of the node on the host switch

pnniMapNodeExtForeNodalFlags.name: pnniMapNodeExtForeNodalFlags
pnniMapNodeExtForeNodalFlags.description: A bit vector indicating the status of several flags on the node

pnniMapNodeIpAddrTable.name: pnniMapNodeIpAddrTable
pnniMapNodeIpAddrTable.description: A table containing the configured IP address of the map nodes. The key is formed by combining the local node index, the remote node id, and the IP address.

pnniMapNodeIpAddrEntry.name: pnniMapNodeIpAddrEntry
pnniMapNodeIpAddrEntry.description: An entry in the switch IP address table.

pnniMapNodeIpAddr.name: pnniMapNodeIpAddr
pnniMapNodeIpAddr.description: The ip address of an interface

pnniMapNodeIpAddrIfName.name: pnniMapNodeIpAddrIfName
pnniMapNodeIpAddrIfName.description: The name of the IP address interface
